      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can absolutely manage this with consistent care, but setting a firm expectation for \"tomorrow morning\" is too optimistic. Applying the peroxide rinse three to four times daily, followed by a thick layer of the antibiotic cream, is a solid regimen. Keep an eye on the drainage; if it turns thick green or the pain spikes, you need to escalate your care immediately. Trust your instincts, and if it looks worse, call them—it's better to be safe than to risk a complication.",
